    slug: "ashra-zil-hajja-eid-ul-adha-aur-qurbani",
    description: `Ashra Zil Hajja - Eid ul Adha aur Qurbani is an Urdu-language Islamic book that provides a comprehensive guide to the first ten days of Dhul Hijjah, the significance of Eid ul Adha, and the rulings and procedures related to the ritual sacrifice (qurbani). The title refers to the blessed ten days beginning from the 1st of Dhul Hijjah through Eid ul Adha and the days of Tashreeq, which are widely regarded in Islamic tradition as the most virtuous days of the entire year. The Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) emphasized the importance of these days in multiple hadith, stating that no good deeds performed during them are more beloved to Allah. This book systematically presents the virtues, recommended acts of worship, and specific obligations associated with this sacred period, making it a practical reference for Muslims who want to maximize their spiritual benefit during Dhul Hijjah.

The book covers the topic of qurbani in thorough detail, addressing the obligatory nature of the sacrifice according to the Hanafi school and its status as a strongly recommended sunnah in other schools of Islamic jurisprudence. It explains the conditions that make a person liable for qurbani, including ownership of the nisab (minimum wealth threshold), the types of animals that are permissible for sacrifice, their minimum age requirements, and the qualities that render an animal suitable or unsuitable for the ritual. The book provides step-by-step instructions for performing the sacrifice, including the proper method of slaughtering, the relevant supplications, and the division of the meat into three portions — one for personal consumption, one for family and friends, and one for the poor and needy. It also addresses common questions and contemporary issues related to qurbani, such as whether one can appoint someone else to perform the sacrifice on their behalf, the ruling on combining shares for a larger animal like a cow or camel, and the permissibility of donating the sacrifice to charitable organizations.

Beyond qurbani, the book details the rituals of Hajj that occur during these ten days and explains the significance of fasting on the Day of Arafah for non-pilgrims, which the Prophet described as expiating the sins of the previous year and the coming year. The section on Eid ul Adha covers the sunnah acts of the day of Eid, including the Eid prayer, takbeerat, and the recommended practices that should be observed. Written in clear, accessible Urdu, this book serves as a practical guide for households, imams preparing Eid sermons, and Islamic school teachers who need a reliable reference on the fiqh of Dhul Hijjah and qurbani.`,
    metaDescription: "Ashra Zil Hajja - Eid ul Adha aur Qurbani is a comprehensive Urdu guide to Dhul Hijjah, Eid sacrifice rulings, and the ten blessed days of Hajj."
